rComments: Okay class. Good books. She was incredibly sweet but class was boring. Very factual and she doesn't leave much room for theory. You read a book, class covers the plot and facts about the author and a few themes. Book load keeps you on your feet, but is pleasurable, just right. She could have done better with lectures, made them more interesting.

Strong Marxist-feminist political ideology throughout class went unidentified. Was frequently unwilling to address questions outside of what canned answers she had already prepared. Frequent mistakes in punctuation and grammar as well as occasional erroneous "facts" about texts being used. I do not recommend this individual on a professional level.

Not really the best class in the world. Sometimes it felt like I was sitting back in high school. She's a sweetheart and holy crap is her diction INSANE. She uses words I've never heard or read anywhere. But the intellectual level of this class was low.
Speak up in class, if not everyone participates quizzes are given. Essay due every other week. Very pleasant woman and gives GREAT feedback on essays.

She runs a straight forward class. She provides a clear syllabus and follows it. So whatever you may do wrong is simply your own fault. The class requires a lot of reading. Discussions in class are interesting but that largely depends on the composition of your classmates. I was fortunate enough to be in the company of  a great group of students.

Great professor teaching Merrill Core course. I thought she carried the class rather nicely. Only problem I think is that the class moves fairly slow when in session and the homework ridiculously hops from books and essays are due every other week. The final is very difficult and will take a lot of studying to pass, but it's due to the department.

Taught the class like it was discussion. Instead of leading in depth analyses, she seemed to be more concerned with ensuring that everyone was excited about the material, which was dry for the most part. While the texts were appropriate, the reading was very intensive. I felt shafted when my hard work was repaid with her superficial lectures.

Sweet God, do not take any classes with her. What a bore. Her notes are from Wikipedia. The lectures are only good for signing in to prove that you go to class. It felt like a history class rather than a lit class. She gives these stupid little quizzes to make sure you keep up on the boring reading. The TAs are smarter than her. Big surprise.

Discussions were engaging, but mostly due to students leadership and willingness to participate. She's nice and really easy going, but her knowledge in the subjects for the most part didnt exceed that of the students.
She's an awesome teacher and i learned a lot from her. she's super nice and friendly. She really helped me improve my writing skills.
Fair, helpful, friendly, and in all other ways cool to work with/learn from. I don't think she's capable of being mean, but she won't let a class walk all over her, either (Mine tried).
